   433	      await new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
   434	        proc.on('error', (err) => {
   435	          cleanupFunc?.();
```

**Fix**: Wrap the post-`prepareCommand` execution setup and process wait in `try`/`finally`, or use an equivalent exactly-once cleanup guard, so cleanup runs for normal close, error events, early generator close, and synchronous throws during `spawn`/stream setup.
